## Checklist before emitting

The JSON Schema is the contract (required fields, nullability, enums, lengths). The reminders below cover the non-structural bits the schema cannot catch.

- [ ] `description`: 1–3 sentences, factual, no marketing fluff.
- [ ] `members.oneLiner`: verifiably sourced — never paraphrased from the `memberPosition`.
- [ ] `members.xLink`: each X handle has been WebFetched and the profile bio confirms affiliation with this protocol.
- [ ] `members.avatarUrl`: `https://unavatar.io/x/<handle>?fallback=false` (or `/github/<handle>?fallback=false`) for each verified handle, else `null`. Never scrape `pbs.twimg.com`.
- [ ] `fundingRounds`: **newest first AND complete history** — if the latest is Series B, Seed and Series A must also be present.
- [ ] `audits.items`: newest first; same firm with different scope = separate entries.
- [ ] `audits.lastScannedAt`: emit any valid `YYYY-MM-DD` (the crawler shell overwrites it with today's UTC date).
- [ ] `sources`: the URLs you actually WebFetched (audit trail only; stripped before DB import).

Emit the single JSON object now. No prose.
